OL,5,FThe broader economic arguments over
OL,6,Fwhether it would be beneficial to allow
OL,7,Fmore advertising need proper scrutiny.
OL,9,FBut given that the public hardly seem
OL,10,Fto have noticed the current rise, it's
OL,11,Fhard to suggest viewers will lose out
OL,12,Ftoo much. Perhaps some newspaper
OL,13,Fjournalists need to watch more TV?
OL,15,FOfcom is seeking views until next week
OL,16,Fover whether to look at relaxing the
OL,17,Frestrictions affecting advertising on
OL,18,FPSBs. It will then decide whether to
OL,19,Frun a full consultation on any proposed
OL,20,Fchanges.
OL,3,CAre we getting a taste of potential new
OL,4,Cad rules for commercial PSBs?
